Regarding [Jon Skeet&#39;s answer on this question](https://stackoverflow.com/a/1467940/7294647), specifically: _&quot;There&#39;s no such thing as a `List&lt;int&gt;` in Java - generics don&#39;t support primitives. Autoboxing only happens for a single element, not for arrays of primitives.&quot;_ –&#160;the answer does not address why generics don&#39;t support primitives, nor why autoboxing only happens for a single element, which is the intent of this question.

